{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὕπνος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>sleep, slumber,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.245, +others (see. below) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>the sleep of death,</b> κοιμήσατο χάλκεον ὕ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.241; Κάλχανθ᾽ ὕ. θανάτοιο κάλυψεν 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Fragmenta” 160 codices 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus; ὕπνῳ καὶ καμάτῳ ἀρημένος 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.2, compare 12.281; τάπητες μαλακώτεροι ὕπνω 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.125, compare 5.51.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] — Special phrases: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of going to <b>sleep,</b> μιν ἐπήλυθε.. ὕ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.793; ἐπὶ.. ὕ. ὄρουσεν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.232; ἱκάνει 1.610; ἔχει 10.4, etc.; τὸν ὕ. ἔμαρπτε 23.62, +others; ᾕρει 24.4, +others; λαμβάνει 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 767; opposed to ὕπνος ἀνῆκέ τινα 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.71, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.551, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 310d: of persons, ὕπνον ἀωτεῖν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.159, etc.; ὕπνου δῶρον ἕλοντο 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.481, etc.; λαβεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 223b; κοιμᾶσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Hiero” 6.7; ἡδὺν ὕπνον καθεύδειν 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Kith.fragment” 1.5; ὕπνου τυχεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 713; μικρὸν ὕπνου λαχών 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.1.11; ὕπνου λαχεῖν μέρος 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 218 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν ὕπνῳ or ὕπνῳ πεσεῖν to fall a-<b>sleep,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).23(41), 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 68; εἰς ὕπνον πεσεῖν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 826 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐχ ὕπνῳ γ᾽ ἐνδόντα (so Badham for εὕδοντά) μ᾽ ἐξεγείρετε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “OT” 65 \">Refs</a>]; also ὕπνῳ δεδμημένος, δαμείς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.2, 14.353, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; νικώμενος, κρατηθεῖσ᾽, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 290, “Eu.” 148 (Lyric poetry); κάτοχος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 978 (Lyric poetry); σκεδάσαι.. ἀπὸ βλεφάρων ὕπνον [prev. work] 991 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> of waking from sleep, ἐγεῖραί τινα ἐξ ὕπνου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.44, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: of the sleeper, ἀνόρουσε, ἔγρετο, ἐξ ὕ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.162, 2.41; ἐξ ὕ. στῆναι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 277; ἀπολακτίσασ᾽ ὕπνον 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 141; ἀποσείσασθαι 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Tim.” 6. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> with Preps., when the <i>plural</i> also is not uncommon, ἐν ὕπνῳ in <b>sleep,</b> in <b>a dream,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 44, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 476c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν τοῖς ὕ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 572b, “Sph.” 266b, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 9.21, “PCair.Zen.” 34.5 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; καθ᾽ ὕπνον ὄντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 970 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 800a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; καθ᾽ ὕπνον, κατὰ τοὺς ὕπνους, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.717e,555b, “Alex.” 50 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; περὶ πρῶτον ὕ. about one's first <b>sleep,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 31, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.2; περὶ πρώτους ὕ. 4th c.BC: Eubulus Comicus 13; ἀπὸ πρώτου ὕ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.43; διὰ μέσων τῶν ὕ. 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Themistocles” 28; ἐκ τῶν ὕ. ἐγείρεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 330e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, <b>dreams,</b> ὕ. ἀγένητοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “D.” 1.22. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>Sleep,</b> as a god, twinbrother of Death, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.231, 16.672, 682; _accusative_ to 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 212 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], son of Night without father. [ῠ by nature, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 3, “Ag.” 14, 912, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ῡ by position in <i>Epic dialect</i>, etc.] (Cf. Sanskrit <i>svápati</i> 'sleep', <i>substantive</i> <b>svápnas</b> 'sleep, dream'; Latin <i>somnus, sopor,</i> etc.)","strongNumber":"G5258","accentedUnicode":"ὕπνος","shortDef":"sleep, slumber","mediumDef":"sleep, slumber <br /><b>sleep,</b> <ref='Mat.1.24'>Mt. 1:24</ref>; <ref='Luk.9.32'>Lk. 9:32</ref>; <ref='Jhn.11.13'>Jn. 11:13</ref>; <ref='Act.20.9'>Acts 20:9;</ref> <i>metaphorically</i> spiritual <b>sleep,</b> religious <b>slumber,</b> <ref='Rom.13.11'>Rom. 13:11</ref>*","stepGloss":"sleep","stepTransliteration":"hupnos","count":6,"_es_Definition":"sueño","_zh_tw_Definition":"睡覺","_zh_Definition":"睡觉","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"giấc ngủ; ngủ","_zh_tw_Gloss":"睡覺, 睡","_es_Gloss":"sueño","_zh_Gloss":"睡觉, 睡"}]}